(11, 'CP100205001', 'auto', 5, 'comp', 'LIC AUTO- COMPREHENSIVE POLICY', 'Motor Insurance Policy- Comprehensive Car Insurance\r\n\r\n In Car insurance, comprehensive coverage covers damage to your vehicle caused by certain events. These include (but are not limited to) fire, theft, vandalism and falling objects. This also comes with a deductible you volunteer to pay and which you are obliged to pay before the insurance company pays the remainder. It is advisable to buy the Comprehensive insurance policy because it covers the insured, vehicle and third party in a single policy.  This type of insurance covers all the risks covered in the Motor Vehicles Act plus loss or damage caused to the vehicle due to: \r\n1.Flood, hurricane, cyclones, typhoon, storm\r\n2.Theft, burglary, strikes and riots\r\n3.Terrorism, Malicious acts\r\n4.Accident, Fire or Theft.\r\n5.Floods and earthquake\r\n6.Transit by road, rail, watercraft, air, elevator, etc.\r\n7.Towing charges incurred after an accident. \r\n8.Explosion, self-ignition, lightning\r\n\r\n The Comprehensive Insurance coverage excludes the loss or damage caused due to:\r\n \r\na.      Driver under the influence of alcohol at the time of impact.\r\n b.      Vehicle being driven by a person not holding a valid driving license.\r\n c.      Damage to the tyres unless the vehicle is also damaged.\r\n d.      Wear and tear or mechanical breakdown.', '', '', '', '', 'Bmw', '118I', '1.8L : 5 Seater : A', '1', 1, '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', 1, '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '1', '800', '2013-01-10 00:13:51', '2013-05-22 05:47:14'),
(12, 'TPL100205001', 'auto', 5, 'tpl', 'LIC AUTO- TPL POLICY', 'Motor TPL insurance\r\nMotor TPL insurance is part of the everyday life of every vehicle owner as all vehicles registered in Estonia must be insured with motor TPL insurance. Motor TPL insurance, which is regulated by law, indemnifies the loss caused by the driver to others in an accident and also any medical costs of the driver, if necessary. \r\n\r\nMotor TPL insurance contract is free and entered into for an unspecified term, but does not automatically provide full insurance coverage. In addition to the regular contract, a policy must be bought for a specified term, which grants the right to use the vehicle, as well as full insurance coverage. The term of the policy may be 1 day to 12 months depending on the wishes of the policyholder. \r\n\r\nEntry into the contract\r\n \r\nWhen entering into a motor TPL insurance contract, you can choose between one of two options. \r\nYes-contract, where ERGO automatically sends you a new policy when the previous one expires.\r\n\r\nNo-contract, where your contract becomes premium-free at the expiry of your policy. You have to keep an eye on the term of your policy to make sure you buy a new one at the right time. The vehicle cannot be used in traffic during the period when your contract is premium-free. \r\nYou should keep in mind that when an invoice for motor third party liability insurance is issued, the recipient of the invoice must pay it, as a contract cannot be changed into a yes-contract or no-contract retrospectively. If you do not wish to receive new policies by post, change your contract to a no-contract at the nearest ERGO branch or by e-mail.\r\n \r\nIf you use the vehicle all year round, a yes-contract is the easiest and cheapest option for you, as it means that ERGO posts or e-mails the new policy to you at the right time. It allows you to save valuable time and money, because policies tied to yes-contracts are cheaper. The policy is also cheaper if you buy it for at least three months or more.\r\n \r\nA regular motor TPL insurance contract from ERGO can be entered into at all ERGO branches and by agents (insurance brokers, credit institutions).', '4x4', '4', '4', '5', '', '', '', '0', 0, '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', 1, '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '100', '100', '1', '1', '800', '2013-01-10 00:23:07', '2013-05-22 05:47:14'),
