(13, 'Al-Sagr tips for a better life', '<div>Tips to prevent cooking fires:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Never leave cooking unattended - Two out of five deaths in home cooking fires occur because the cooking was unattended.</li>\r\n    <li>Keep cooking area clean - Always wipe appliances and surfaces after cooking to prevent grease buildup.</li>\r\n    <li>Do not store flammable objects near the stove - Curtains, pot holders, dish towels and food packaging can easily catch fire.</li>\r\n    <li>Always turn pot handles toward the center of the stove - Turning handles inward can prevent pots from being knocked off the stove or pulled down by small children.</li>\r\n    <li>Wear short or close-fitting sleeves when cooking - Fires can occur when clothing comes in contact with stovetop burners.</li>\r\n    <li>Heat cooking oil slowly - Heating oil too quickly can easily start a fire. Never leave hot oil unattended.</li>\r\n    <li>Teach children safe cooking - Young children should be kept at least 3 feet (1 meter) away from the stove while older family members are cooking. Older children should cook only with permission and under the supervision of an adult.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Al-Sagr tips for a better life', '<div>Tips to prevent cooking fires:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Never leave cooking unattended - Two out of five deaths in home cooking fires occur because the cooking was unattended.</li>\r\n    <li>Keep cooking area clean - Always wipe appliances and surfaces after cooking to prevent grease buildup.</li>\r\n    <li>Do not store flammable objects near the stove - Curtains, pot holders, dish towels and food packaging can easily catch fire.</li>\r\n    <li>Always turn pot handles toward the center of the stove - Turning handles inward can prevent pots from being knocked off the stove or pulled down by small children.</li>\r\n    <li>Wear short or close-fitting sleeves when cooking - Fires can occur when clothing comes in contact with stovetop burners.</li>\r\n    <li>Heat cooking oil slowly - Heating oil too quickly can easily start a fire. Never leave hot oil unattended.</li>\r\n    <li>Teach children safe cooking - Young children should be kept at least 3 feet (1 meter) away from the stove while older family members are cooking. Older children should cook only with permission and under the supervision of an adult.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Al-Sagr tips for a better life', 'Al-Sagr tips for a better life', 0, 0, 0, '2014-06-09 00:36:46'),
